'''Gunnar Eriksson''' ([[September 13]] [[1921]] &ndash; [[July 8]], [[1982]]) was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[cross-country skiing|cross-country skier]] who competed in the 1940's. He won the 4 x 10 km gold and the 18 km bronze at the [[1948 Winter Olympics]] in [[St. Moritz]]

Eriksson also won the 50 km event at the [[1950 FIS Nordic World Ski Championships]] in [[Lake Placid, New York]].

